This script extracts the score from each frame (displayed at the top left) and appends it to the filename. If
--output_dir is specified, a new copy of each frame is saved in the provided output directory. If --output_dir is not
specified, the original input images are renamed.

Sample usage:
/usr/bin/python2.7 /home/josh/grade_17/cs231n/fox-net/src/main/reward/knn_extract_reward.py \
    --template_dir=/home/josh/grade_17/cs231n/fox-net/data/reward/templates/* \
    --input_dir=/home/josh/grade_17/cs231n/fox-net/data/data_score_health_test/data/* \
    --output_dir=/home/josh/grade_17/cs231n/fox-net/data/data_score_health_test_classified/

/usr/bin/python2.7 /home/josh/grade_17/cs231n/fox-net/src/main/reward/knn_extract_reward.py \
    --template_dir=/home/josh/grade_17/cs231n/fox-net/data/reward/templates/* \
    --input_dir=/home/josh/grade_17/cs231n/fox-net/data/data_053017/test/*
    --output_dir=/home/josh/grade_17/cs231n/fox-net/data/data_053017/test_classified